  "body": "Forces `requestIdleCallback` to fire if too much time has elapsed, even if the main thread is busy. Required to make expiration times work properly. Otherwise, async work can expire, but React never has a chance to flush it because the browser never calls into React.\r\n\r\nTo demonstrate, I added a new fixture. The fixture clogs the main thread using `setInterval`, and increments a counter inside a `didUpdate` loop. The counter will only increment after each update expires.\r\n\r\n![aagomaghj8](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3624098/32807814-01feb40c-c946-11e7-8689-bcf576a4389d.gif)\r\n",
